🔬 Real-world evidence

This isn’t just theory—we’ve observed effects caused by it:

* Casimir Effect
    Two metal plates in a vacuum get pulled together because of vacuum energy differences
* Atomic behavior at very low temperatures
* Quantum harmonic oscillators (lab-tested systems)

